B. Factors 

This section relates to the social / economic and political situation of the constituency

1. Region – super region of the constituency

Now there is a lot of debate on how to divide the regions in Tamil Nadu. While there is an obvious difference in the politics of the regions, the boundaries are very grey. For our analysis, I am defining the regions in my own way – this has to be as all the other classifications have their own differences and I need something I agree with completely. The logic of the division is explained below. 

I have divided the state into five regions : Greater Chennai, North, Kongu, Delta and South.

The unit of division here is the district. A constituency will be included in the region that a majority of the district falls into, even if individually it is closer to another region. The sub-regional grouping [subsection 2] tries to correct for this.

a. Greater Chennai : this region is usually just called Chennai, but I thought this sounds grander. 

Districts [1] : Chennai

b. North : this region is the northern part of Tamil Nadu. I have tried to bring in the areas which have two types of politics – firstly almost the full extent of PMK politics and secondly DMDK politics. Because of this, I have also included Cuddalore district in the North [some put it in Delta region]. I have also left out Salem to Kongu. North is by far the biggest region.

Districts [12] : Tiruvallur, Kanchipuram, Chengalpattu, Vellore, Ranipet, Tirupattur, Krishnagiri, Dharmapuri, Tiruvannamalai, Villupuram, Kallakurichi and Cuddalore

c. Kongu : this is the western region of Tamil Nadu. I have tried to stick as close to Kongunadu boundaries as possible – expect Krishnagiri and Dharmapuri which went to north. The other choice that had to be made was Dindigul. While I was sure it went to South, in most groupings its included in Kongu. Some of the constituencies are more like Kongu and some like South TN. I have included into Kongu anyway as this seems to be a larger part.

Districts [8] : Salem, Namakkal, Erode, Tiruppur, Nilgiris, Coimbatore, Dindigul and Karur

d. Delta : comprises of the districts on the Kaveri delta. The only question here was  about Pudukottai, which I have included in South instead of here.

Districts [7] : Tiruchirappalli, Perambalur, Ariyalur, Mayiladuthurai, Nagapattinam, Tiruvarur, Thanjavur

e.  South :comprising the entire of South Tamil Nadu – basically Pandyanadu.

Districts [10] : Pudukottai, Sivaganga, Madurai, Theni, Virudhunagar, Ramanathapuram, Thoothukudi, Tenkasi, Tirunelvel and Kanniyakumari





