4. Urbanism – the rough level of urbanisation

Here again the classification gets a little bit more murky. Its easy get the cities but after that it gets more difficult.

a. Metro : I have taken only the 16 constituencies in the central Chennai area. This division actually corresponds to the Chennai region usually taken for regional analysis of Chennai.

b. City : here I have actually included the list of cities in Tamil Nadu with corporation area population over 100000. The list can be accessed at :
https://nskfdc.nic.in/writereaddata/files/1Lakh_and_Above.xlsx and https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cities_in_Tamil_Nadu_by_population

I have also considered the constituencies in Chennai district that are not a metro as cities. In cities with multiple constituencies named after directions, I have included all of them as cities. In just the case of Coimbatore, I have included Singanallur as a city as it is geographically the same.

c. Town : here is where I have had most amount of trouble. Given the spread of towns and the high degree of urbanisation in many villages, however we classify, we will have trouble. For this, I am using a very simplistic division. There is a list of every municipality in Tamil Nadu accessed from :
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_towns_in_Tamil_Nadu_by_population . The original links arent opening so I am settling for this.

For now I have included all constituencies which have a municipality within its borders as Town. I have also included some constituencies at the border of cities which have a spillover of urbanisation as Towns.

I need all of your help in recategorising them into Town [Main] constituencies like Tiruchengode or Town [Rural] constituencies like Harur and Yercaud. There is no strict criteria for this, so we will have to make one.

d. Rural : where there is no municipality


