7. Leader – constituencies of party leaders

I have only taken few. To be qualified, you need to be the leader of the party in an alliance [or individually] able to capture state power. The party needs to have stood in atleast two seats too. The leader should also have featured in the top five results of the constituency.


8. Satrapy – the individual kottais of people [after 1967]

This has been my favourite to define. There are two types of satrapies – current and legacy. Current applies to sitting MLAs.

To be a satrap, you need to :
	Have held a seat atleast once [to filter out alternate victories]
	Have won a seat with atleast thrice 
	
This also removes just two time MLAs and breakaway MLAs eg – INC to TMC just once

The satrapy is coded with the party of the satrap. In case there has been a party switch, the party they defected to has been chosen.

Satrapies of both parties are coded with both parties, latest coming first.                                        

9. Legacy Satrapy

Older Satrapies are stored here. In case it has been two parties, the later party is written first

10. Kottai

If any party [not including breakaways] has managed to win the last three elections in a row [not including by-elections] it becomes a kottai. 


11. Legacy Kottai

Older kottais without a sitting MLA in that party. In case there are two kottais, the later is coded first. Legacy kottais need a four election streak to be counted.


12. Legacy – where the tallest shadows were cast

Any constituency where Kamarajar, Anna, Kalaignar, MGR , Amma or Captain has contested

In case more than one person has contested, the earlier person is code 


C. Base Data

This section deals with the basic electoral database

10. Electorate : total eligible electorate

11. Turnout : total number of votes cast

12. Turnout % : (turnout / electorate) * 100

13. Margin : margin of victory. Calculated as alliance one votes – alliance two votes

14. Margin % : (margin / turnout) * 100

15. Anna Index : my greatest contribution to Tamil Nadu political analysis [just the name]. The index is the sum of the vote shares gathered by the DMK alliance and AIADMK alliance. It essentially shows the percentage of people voting for the two Dravidian majors.

D. Election-wise results

This section deals with the results of the parties with the five highest votes in each constituency. Why did I choose just five – convenience mostly.
The section is divided into First, Second, Third, Fourth and Fifth in order of the parties with the highest to lowest votes.

16. Alliance : Coded as DMK+, AIADMK+, NTK, PFA, PF, Independant and NOTA

17. Party : Some of the one seat parties are just coded with the symbol they stood in

18. Name : I have removed all . Between the initials. I have kept the original spelling for each. People who have the place names as prefixes, I have retained only if they are an official satrap

19. Vote : total votes

20. Vote Share : (votes / turnout) * 100

The same repeats in this order for the next four results.
